def principal_component_regression(x, y):
    """
    Resources:
    https://scikit-learn.org/stable/auto_examples/cross_decomposition/plot_pcr_vs_pls.html
    """
    x_scaled = (x-np.mean(x))/np.std(x)
    y_scaled = (y-np.mean(y))/np.std(y)
    x_stack = np.column_stack((list(x_scaled),list(y_scaled)))
    pca = PCA(n_components=2).fit(x_stack)
    for i, (comp, var) in enumerate(zip(pca.components_, pca.explained_variance_)):
        if i == 0:  # The first component explains most of the variance
#             print(comp, var)
            comp = comp * var  # scale component by its variance explanation power
            lin_fit = np.polyfit([0, comp[0]],[0, comp[1]],1)
            fit_x = np.arange(-2,2,0.01)
            y_hat = np.polyval(lin_fit, fit_x)
    return np.polyfit(fit_x*np.std(x)+np.mean(x), y_hat*np.std(y)+np.mean(y), 1)


def density_scatter(x,y):
    xy = np.vstack([x,y])
    z = gaussian_kde(xy)(xy)
    return z

def get_protein_slope_dict(dataframe):
    
    onen_dict = pd.Series(dataframe['Protien Slope (1-N)'].values, index=dataframe.Uniprot).to_dict()
    mltn_dict = pd.Series(dataframe['Protien Slope (multi-N)'].values, index=dataframe.Uniprot).to_dict()
    
    return onen_dict, mltn_dict

def assemgle_protein_slope_dataframe(dataframe_exp1, dataframe_exp2):
    
    onen_dict_exp1, mltn_dict_exp1 = get_protein_slope_dict(dataframe_exp1)
    onen_dict_exp2, mltn_dict_exp2 = get_protein_slope_dict(dataframe_exp2)
    
    slope_df = pd.DataFrame()
    slope_df['Uniprot'] = np.unique(list(onen_dict_exp1.keys())+list(onen_dict_exp2.keys()))
    slope_df['slope_1N_exp1'] = slope_df.Uniprot.map(onen_dict_exp1)
    slope_df['slope_1N_exp2'] = slope_df.Uniprot.map(onen_dict_exp2)
    slope_df['slope_mltN_exp1'] = slope_df.Uniprot.map(mltn_dict_exp1)
    slope_df['slope_mltN_exp2'] = slope_df.Uniprot.map(mltn_dict_exp2)
    
    return slope_df

def get_ion_intensity_and_ori_distance(misc_df, slope_df):
    
    ori_dict = pd.Series(misc_df['Circular distance from oriC'].values, index = misc_df['Entry']).to_dict()
    ion_dict = pd.Series(misc_df['Summed ion intensity / Length'].values, index = misc_df['Entry']).to_dict()
    
    slope_df['ori_distance'] = slope_df.Uniprot.map(ori_dict)
    slope_df['ion_intensity'] = slope_df.Uniprot.map(ion_dict)
    slope_df['mean_slope_1N'] = (slope_df['slope_1N_exp1']+slope_df['slope_1N_exp2'])/2
    slope_df['mean_slope_mltN'] = (slope_df['slope_mltN_exp1']+slope_df['slope_mltN_exp2'])/2
    
    return slope_df

The effects of the gene location around the origin on the protein slope¶

The circular distance of the gene from the oriC is plotted against the protein slope. The average slope from two biological replicates is plotted for each protein.

def plot_ion_intensity_and_ori_distance_with_slope(slope_df, ion_bin_n, ori_bin_n, save_path):
    
    
    plot_df = slope_df[slope_df.ion_intensity>0]
    plot_df = slope_df[~slope_df.ori_distance.isnull()]
    plot_df['ori_distance'] = plot_df.ori_distance/10**6
    plot_df['ori_bin'] = pd.qcut(plot_df.ori_distance, ori_bin_n)
    plot_df.replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan, inplace=True)
    plot_df = plot_df[['ori_distance', 'mean_slope_1N', 'mean_slope_mltN', 'ori_bin']].dropna()
    print(plot_df.shape[0], 'proteins')
    print(plot_df.sort_values('ori_distance').ori_bin.value_counts())
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
    gs = matplotlib.gridspec.GridSpec(1, 3, height_ratios=[1], width_ratios=[0.2]*3)
    gss = [plt.subplot(gs[0,0]),
           plt.subplot(gs[0,2])]
    one_axis = gss[0]
    two_axis = gss[1]
    
#     plt.figure(figsize=(2,5))
    one_axis.set_title('1N-rich cells', fontweight='bold', fontsize=14)
#     z = density_scatter(plot_df.ori_distance, plot_df.mean_slope_1N)
    one_axis.plot(plot_df.ori_distance, plot_df.mean_slope_1N, 'o', color='lightgray', markersize=4)
#     one_axis.scatter(plot_df.ori_distance, plot_df.mean_slope_1N, c=z, s=4, cmap='Greys')
    mean_df = plot_df.groupby('ori_bin').mean()
    std_df = plot_df.groupby('ori_bin').sem()
    one_axis.errorbar(mean_df.ori_distance, mean_df.mean_slope_1N, yerr=std_df.mean_slope_1N,
                marker='o', markersize=10, markerfacecolor='none',ls='none', color='red')
    one_axis.axhline([0], linewidth=0.5, color='black')
#     print(spearmanr(plot_df.ori_distance, plot_df.mean_slope_1N))
    one_axis.set_xlabel('Circular distance\nfrom oriC (Mbps)', fontweight='bold', fontsize=14)
    one_axis.set_ylabel('Protein slope', fontweight='bold', fontsize=14)
    one_axis.set_ylim(-1.25,1.25)
#     plt.show()

    fit_df = plot_df[plot_df.ori_distance<1.35]
    fit = np.polyfit(fit_df.ori_distance, fit_df.mean_slope_1N, 1)
    x_fit = np.arange(0,plot_df.ori_distance.max(),0.01)
#     one_axis.plot(x_fit, np.polyval(fit, x_fit), color='red')
#     print(fit, 'linear fit, 1N')
    print('1N-rich', spearmanr(fit_df.ori_distance, fit_df.mean_slope_1N), 'Spearman r below 1.35')

#     plt.figure(figsize=(2,5))
    two_axis.set_title('multi-N cells', fontweight='bold', fontsize=14)
    two_axis.plot(plot_df.ori_distance, plot_df.mean_slope_mltN, 'o', color='lightgray', markersize=4)
    mean_df = plot_df.groupby('ori_bin').mean()
    std_df = plot_df.groupby('ori_bin').sem()
    two_axis.errorbar(mean_df.ori_distance, mean_df.mean_slope_mltN, yerr=std_df.mean_slope_mltN,
                marker='o', markersize=10, markerfacecolor='none',ls='none', color='blue')
    two_axis.axhline([0], linewidth=0.5, color='black')
    print('multi-N', spearmanr(plot_df.ori_distance, plot_df.mean_slope_mltN))
    two_axis.set_xlabel('Circular distance\nfrom oriC (Mbps)', fontweight='bold', fontsize=14)
#     two_axis.set_ylabel('Protein slope', fontweight='bold', fontsize=14)
    two_axis.set_ylim(-1.25,1.25)
    
    if os.path.isdir(save_path):
        print('saving...')
        plt.savefig(save_path+'/distance_from_oriC.eps')
    
    plt.show()
    
    
    
    plot_df = slope_df[slope_df.ion_intensity>0]
    plot_df = slope_df[~slope_df.ori_distance.isnull()]
    plot_df['ori_distance'] = plot_df.ori_distance/10**6
    plot_df['log_intensity'] = np.log10(plot_df.ion_intensity)
    plot_df['ori_bin'] = pd.qcut(plot_df.ori_distance, ori_bin_n)
    plot_df.replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan, inplace=True)
    plot_df = plot_df[['ori_distance', 'ori_bin', 'log_intensity']].dropna()
    print(plot_df.shape[0], 'proteins')

#     print(mean_df)

                marker='o', markersize=10, markerfacecolor='none',ls='none', color='black')

    plt.ylabel('Summed ion intensity /\nsequence length (log$_{10}$)', fontweight='bold', fontsize=14)
    plt.xlabel('Circular distance\nfrom oriC (Mbps)', fontweight='bold', fontsize=14)
    
    if os.path.isdir(save_path):
        print('saving...')
        plt.savefig(save_path+'/distance_from_oriC_vs_summed_ion_intensity.eps')
    
    plt.show()

Comparison between the protein and mRNA slopes¶

The average mRNA slope from two biological replicates is compared with the average protein slope from two biological replicates.

In [11]:
def plot_rna_experiment_slope_comparison(rna_dataframe, save_path):
    
    def remove_nans(x, y):
        plot_df = pd.DataFrame()
        plot_df['x'] = x
        plot_df['y'] = y
        plot_df = plot_df.dropna()
        return plot_df.x, plot_df.y
    
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,4))
    gs = matplotlib.gridspec.GridSpec(1, 6, height_ratios=[1], width_ratios=[1,0.1,0.2]*2)
    gss = [plt.subplot(gs[0,0]),
           plt.subplot(gs[0,1]),
           plt.subplot(gs[0,3]),
           plt.subplot(gs[0,4])]
    
    one_axis = gss[0]
    one_density_axis = gss[1]
    two_axis = gss[2]
    two_density_axis = gss[3]
    
    xone = rna_dataframe['RNA_slope_exp230501']
    yone = rna_dataframe['RNA_slope_exp230502']
    xone, yone = remove_nans(xone, yone)
    zone = density_scatter(xone, yone)
    print('Copmarison of RNAseq replciates',spearmanr(xone, yone))
    
    xtwo = rna_dataframe['RNA_slope']
    ytwo = rna_dataframe['mean_protein_slope_1N']
    xtwo, ytwo = remove_nans(xtwo, ytwo)
    ztwo = density_scatter(xtwo, ytwo)
    print('Comparison of mRNA and protein slopes', spearmanr(xtwo, ytwo))
    
    fig_one = one_axis.scatter(xone, yone, c=zone, cmap='cividis', s=2)
    one_axis.axhline(0, linewidth=0.5, color='black')
    one_axis.axvline(0, linewidth=0.5, color='black')
    one_axis.set_xlim(-3.5,3.5)
    one_axis.set_ylim(-3.5,3.5)
    print(xone.shape[0], 'mRNAs detected')
    fig_two = two_axis.scatter(xtwo, ytwo, c=ztwo, cmap='cividis', s=2)
    print(xtwo.shape[0], 'mRNA - protein slope pairs')
    pcr = principal_component_regression(xtwo, ytwo)
    x_pcr = np.arange(-3.5,3.51,0.01)
    print('Principal component regression:', pcr)
#     print('Univariate fit:', np.polyfit(xtwo, ytwo, 1))
#     two_axis.plot(x_pcr, np.polyval(pcr, x_pcr), color='black', linewidth=2)
    two_axis.axhline(0, linewidth=0.5, color='black')
    two_axis.axvline(0, linewidth=0.5, color='black')
    two_axis.set_xlim(-3.5,3.5)
    two_axis.set_ylim(-3.5,3.5)

    cbar_one = plt.colorbar(fig_one, cax=one_density_axis)
    cbar_one.set_label('Density', rotation=90, fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
    cbar_two = plt.colorbar(fig_two, cax=two_density_axis)
    cbar_two.set_label('Density', rotation=90, fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
    
    two_axis.set_xlabel('RNA slope', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
    two_axis.set_ylabel('Protein slope', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
    
    one_axis.set_xlabel('RNA slope - Exp #1', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
    one_axis.set_ylabel('RNA slope - Exp #2', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
    
    if os.path.isdir(save_path):
        print('saving...')
        plt.savefig(save_path+'/proteomics_transcriptomics_slope_comparison.eps')
    plt.show()
